reviews: great location - great room - good breakfast service - hotel felt like it was running on a very lean staffing but the employees worked hard! very lively area so be prepared for some noise at night if you at front of building, but, truly, it added to the vibe

Attractive, comfortable, chic hotel in vibrant Marais. Delicious fresh breakfast. Attractive lounge, bar areas. Bright, well designed rooms. 5minutes walk to Metro & easily accessible to sights, restaurants, shopping.

My mother and I spent 6 nights at this wonderful boutique property and enjoyed our time there immensely. Attentive and warm staff, pristine and comfortable conditions and a private, quiet respite from the fabulous, bustling neighborhood filled with every convenience and luxury one would desire. We will be back, for certain - and thank the 9Confidential team for their stellar hospitality.

My daughter and I stayed at this hotel for 7 nights and it was a perfect choice for us. We loved the Marais area and wouldnt have wanted to stay anywhere else. We had a very warm welcome by Emily and Cecile and we were delighted that our room was ready soon after we arrived. We loved our room on the 5th floor. It was very spacious and the decor was so Parisian! Closet space was limited but we made do. We had a large window overlooking the narrow street and although there are bars all around, the noise did not bother us at night. Bed was super comfortable! The staff is friendly and respectful. Overall it was a wonderful experience and I would stay there again.

Charming boutique hotel in a bus selling area. Plenty of great restaurants close by and convenient to access all transportation and the sights of Paris. Comfy bed but could be a little noisy at night so not for the light sleeper.

Carefully designed by Philippe Starck, this hotel is a gem. Super comfortable super well located and quiet inside. Small with a lot of character. Every room is designed for comfort and special attention to the bathroom that includes japanese toilette.

Your stay in the Le Marais is far from a swamp, which is what the name refers to in French. This beautiful hotel and neighborhood in Paris is centrally located to fine shopping, terrific dinning and night life. We would stay here again in a heartbeat, close to Metro, and City Hall, and the Seine River in Paris and steps from Notre Dame

After a very last minute booking, we arrived at the hotel in Marais and had the good fortune of being greeted by Novalia, who went out of her way to ensure we got the next room configuration for our stay. Genuinely she showed care and helped to make our arrival and stay so welcome and pleasant.
The whole team were helpful, making calls and booking dinner as well as any other requests.
I would not hesitate to stay here again and sincerely felt welcome and looked after. This hotel has a great team and wonderful atmosphere  we would definitely stay here again and location is perfect!

From check in to check out we loved 9Confidential! The "team" was friendly and available to help us with everything. Our sunny spacious room gave us a great view and a look at the full moon. The location is wonderful. When we return to Paris we will stay here again. Our stay was perfect!

We had an excellent stay at this wonderful boutique hotel. The service was excellent, the rooms were spacious enough, clean and the staff was second to none. It's in a great location, you can't go wrong.We will definitely stay here again!!

We selected this hotel because of past reviews on Tripadvisor. We loved our stay at this hotel. it is a well located, clean and super cozy hotel. We loved that it was a small, boutique hotel.
1. Location - this location is PERFECT if you want to stay in a lovely neighborhood filled with great shopping and food. It is a few minutes away from the metro station, Hotel de Ville and walked to every part of the city from our hotel.
2. Rooms - we stayed in a Club room which is slightly larger. Bed was super comfortable and room was typical size of a european hotel room.
3. Hotel - we paid for inclusive breakfast which was perfect. The hotel lobby is spacious so you can have coffee or drink in a nice, quiet lounge after being out in the city all day. The staff were very friendly and made a few great restaurant recommendations.

Loved the area. Loved the hotel. It's a small jewel. You can walk everywhere. We stayed in one of the three suites. The courtyard facing windows meant it was very quiet and the views over the rooftops were exquisite.
It rained but that didn't put a damper on our visit.

Great location. Decor is Parisian chic. Breakfast is excellent and convenient for getting an early start to the day. The beds are comfortable and there was sufficient room for 4 suitcases (plus all the shopping bags). It was the perfect home away from home in Paris. I will definitely be back to 9Confidential!

Great little hotel in the Marais very close to all the places you want to go to in the Marais, very central. New hotel opened in 2018, light, bright and airy and very art-deco in style of bedrooms. Staying in a suite is your best choice if you want space. Breakfast is ok but you might want to have something in the many cafe's near the hotel. All in all, a very good clean hotel and wonderful staff
My husband and I loved staying at this hotel for our honeymoon! From the location to the staff and amenities everything was a 10 out of 10! We would absolutely stay here again when we visit France!!!

Very good hotel! I liked the location, the stuff was very kind and the overall is perfect for me. Definitely coming back next time. Definitely recommended. I think one of the best hotel treatment Ive ever had

We arrived and were warmly and warmly welcomed, the staff are all very friendly and helpful, the rooms are mega beautiful and the interior design is eye-catching! Can we only recommend to anyone who wants to have the city also packed in a hotel

This is a beautiful boutique hotel, curated in every detail; small but very comfortable room. The staff is friendly and helpful and the location is perfect to walk around and enjoy this beautiful city. I would definitely stay here again

lIt was a great view from the suite. Like wendys window in Peter Pan. Idealic with the lively cafes right down the street. Quiet to sleep and lively as an option. Right near the Notre Dame. and beuatiful streets to walk to any other arrondissement

This is a small but stylish boutique hotel in the Marais district of Paris. Very central location, comfortable bedrooms, close to sights, amenities, bars and restaurants. Lively area and great to just walk about. Can be a little noisy during weekends.

What a delightful hotel- super clean, elegant and fresh. But the best part was how caring and attentive the staff were. They always greeted me coming in, asking what I needed, how I was, etc. The room was very comfortable and well appointed with all the amenities.

Wonderful staff, cleanliness and location; showers are great. Would feel more luxurious without the knick knacks (pictures everyone, feathers) - that all felt busy and detracted from the decor which clearly has production value.

What a beautiful stay in the heart of Le Marais. This hotel is perfect to explore Paris. It's close to everything one would need, lots of restaurants, bars and coffee shops around. The hotel has clean room, comfortable bed, good shower with all the amenities. The staff are just wonderful, so friendly and helpful. The wifi works great and their breakfast was also delicious. I can't wait to return to this 9Confidentiel.

This is one of my most favorite boutique hotels ever. Wonderful location, service and amenities. The staff was delightful and went out of its way to make sure we were happy. I loved the quasi modern decor which was very pretty. In short, I have nothing but superlatives for describing this hotel and would return in a heartbeat.

This is the 2nd time I have stayed here, could not recommend it more!
The 1st time I stayed there was a group of us as I was working and then it was also excellent. This time I was with my cousin and her disabled daughter. They were so accommodating and warm in their welcome.

Loved this stay!! Such a gorgeously designed hotel in the perfect location. Easy to walk from or take the metro anywhere.

Miriam of the front desk was incredibly helpful + warm, assisting us with dinner reservations. And the bartender (I'm so sorry I forgot his name!) was the one with all of the suggestions, which were all great - local's choices vs. touristic ones.

Highlights:
+ heated bathroom floors!!
+ breakfast buffet (we did not have it included, but ended up having it 3 out of our 5 days there - loved the offerings and quiet setting)
+ the lobby bar to stop for a cocktail before heading out to dinner

The amenities were really lovely: robes, branded slippers, quality bath products, teas + hot water kettle, nespresso machine, hair dryer.

The room was only missing an iron. We had asked for one but it was unavailable. I'm guessing other guest(s) had them and not returned yet. The rooms are good-sized but closets are smaller so it seems they don't already have them in the room. Good thing I over-packed and could choose another outfit!

We will surely be back next time we are in Paris! It's a great value.

Staff and rooms are lovely. But its slightly let down by breakfast and facilities. Dont expect a hairdryer or milk for your tea. Location is excellent in the heart of Marais with bars and clubs right outside. Double glazing mostly works, but book an internal room if you want extra quiet.

Truly 3.5 but Im rounding up. Great location. Upon arrival our bidet didnt work. I had to ask about it every day (5 days) and it still never worked. No one seemed to be too concerned. The manager offered us two glasses of champagne for the trouble.

Luckily I checked the bill before we checked out and they tried to charge us for 4 glasses even though we only had two and they were supposed to be comped.

It was our honeymoon and we informed the hotel and there wasnt anything special which was fine but slightly disappointing.

Although the front staff is very nice, the pictures of the room online dont represent how small the bathroom and shower are. It was extremely small & the room online looked much larger. They had to be suites in the pictures. Also, housekeeping didnt change sheets or provide enough towels or replenish our coffee supplies. We just felt the room was not as advertised and was overpriced considering the size. Also, there was very little counter space or anywhere to store clothing. (Two open shelves and a small hanging area.). I dont know how this was highly rated in different online sites. The bed was comfy and the staff is friendly, but we would have stayed in a different place.

This hotel has a very comfortable and warm charm to it. The bed,pillows,towels, bathrobes and slippers all feel so good after a long day touring the city. Its a nice place to stay in a great area.
My only complaint about this hotel is the management and front desk staff. They are not helpful for the most part.
One of the girls should not be trusted to do anything you ask of her.
The housekeeping staff is amazing

They need to work on their front desk customer service to earn more than four stars.

Delicious and plentiful breakfast included in fare, comfortable room with big windows and high end furnishings and the WiFi was very fast. The location was very convenient to the metro station, major sites and surrounded by great restaurants. Try LAlivi.

Super luxe hotel - the photos don't lie! The front desk staff was super friendly and helpful. The hotel is in a local neighborhood, but still close to all of the tourist attractions. Highly recommend staying here.

Like most Paris hotels, very confined space, but really high-end design and great attention by the staff. On the margin, not cheap for a hotel without fitness center or breakfast--but that's Paris (and plenty of bistros around, and running by the Seine is a great option)!

This is a Small beautiful boutique hotel in a very trendy neighborhood close to everything to walk. Staff is extremely friendly and very accommodating for any needs. Breakfast variety is enough and fresh

Location is an A+. Could not be better. Centrally located just a few blocks from the Hotel De Ville metro station, the hotel is either within walking distance or a short and easy train ride away from most of the major sites. Walkable areas include La Marais, Louvre, Latin Qtr, and St. Germaine. The immediate surrounding area has a fantastic vibe, great shopping, great food, and has more of a local feel to it.

Rooms: The room were fantastic. Serene design. Fantastic bath amenities. Clean, comfortable, and easy to be in. The common areas of the hotel were also gorgeous and provided a serene retreat within a bustling city.

The staff was excellent, top notch and took care of all of our needs. We appreciate them greatly.

Lovely staff in a small hotel that felt really luxurious without the 5 star price or pretentions.
Really nice, spacious lounge areas a real surprise bonus in Paris
Location is great although might not suit everybody

This is a beautiful hotel, very conveniently and centrally located in the Marais. It is charming, the staff was very friendly and the longe bar and rooms were all very lovely. We enjoyed our stay and are looking forward to returning.

Amazing location, fresh design, really well kept! I would definitely go back! New generation Philippe Starck design, with comfortable rooms and gorgeous bathrooms. Very happy with everything at this property.

I had a wonderful stay at 9confidential Hotel. The location in Le Marais is wonderfully central to a lot of good shopping and not far from many excellent restaurants in the 11th. A metro station nearby gives you easy access to other parts of the city.

I asked for a room in the courtyard to avoid any noise from the activities down below at night. It was a good decision. I slept soundly every night - the bed being very comfortable - and the insulation from other rooms being very good.

The room size is fine for central Paris. There are several pleasant accessories in the room. The lobby is small but has a nice bar and very comfortable chairs with magazines in French and English.

Best of all was the service. Noraliza welcomed us when we checked in and always had a pleasant smile for us - and some good advice - when we came in or stepped out. I had a little problem with a misplaced credit card at a store close to the hotel. She helped me resolve the matter without any fuss.

I would definitely stay at 9C again. It gives you everything you hope of a city center hotel and then a little bit more.

Also - do head for Peleton Cafe (a short walk away) for excellent coffee.

Location: prime

Ambience: incredible aromatherapy, kind staff, understanding for disabled guests, and extremely clean

Service: unrivaled

Rooms: spacious, quiet, heated marble floors, awesome showers, quality amenities, great tea/coffee service (BUT WE NEED MILK PLEASE!); incredibly comfortable bed, great STRONG aircon!

Unique Points: guest rooms have names instead of #s, the location is unrivaled yet quiet, wonderful private access; automatic curtains revealing incredible street views

Low Points: Reception (not Emilie) recommended for steak frites we try Chez Julien nearby which is charming and outside. Unfortunately, not only do they NOT serve steak/frites, but the experience is one to AVOID.

This hotel is at best a three star hotel, it needs a new management and serious renovations! For starters, the room arrangement is extremely inconvenient with a toilet in one room, shower in another and sink in the hallway. It all felt dysfunctional and claustrophobic. Second, there are mirrors everywhere in the room lining walls and what have you but there is not one mirror that is not tarnished and has clarity! No way to get dressed up or put on make up. Third, be aware of the location, though it's very close in proximity to shopping and restaurants, it is right down street from very noisy clubs that stay open till 2-4 am. There is no sound proofing in this hotel

I highly recommend this hotel. Wonderful location, very friendly staff, and a fair price.
Restaurants, shopping, Metro, are all around the corner.
I will definitely stay here next time I visit Paris..

We were delighted with our stay in the executive room, which was as quiet as promised. The bed was comfortable and firm, and the pillows were excellent. The staff is very friendly.
The breakfast is entirely satisfactory but we were not blown away by it.

very poor service and unpleasant staff at the reception. Such people should not work in hotels. The room was ugly and smelled bad. Will not stay there again. The location was okay but there are many better hotels in the same area. Would definitely not recommend this hotel to anyone.

Great location, safe, secure, quiet rooms. Great staff. Private lobby bar. Decor is amazing. Will definitely stay again when Im in Paris. Rooms are decent size for Paris. Very comfortable with luxurious finishes.

Excellent hotel !! We stayed at the hotel for five nights in early June 22. The room is charmingly decorated, not big but has it all. The service is excellent and the best location you can ask for. The hotel is suitable for couples and less for two friends. I highly recommend it. We'll be sure to return to it next time we're in Paris

We stayed over 2 periods in May, first time in the Aurore Suite for 5 nights and a week later in Marcelle Suite for 4 nights.

The room is super comfortable for both, the main difference is that Marcelle is just one floor down and it hasn't got the roof top views of the nearby areas.

The furniture and decor are modern comfortable with an extra touch of luxury. Rooms are big for 2 people, the bath is huge, the shower is great, the toilet is fun (it is the Japanese type that will clean your bottom but without the blow drying function).

Lots of hanging spaces (no wardrobe), good sofa and big chair, a big writing desk behind the bed where you can place your luggage on the floor, windows are all double glazed and the curtains are very thick to keep the light out and warmth within, very quiet and sleep very well at night.

But.......

The internet is totally unusable, the TV reception went blank every 2 minutes, spoke to Emilie the Manager and it has been like this for a while and no date is given when it will be fixed, so we have to watch the news several times to get the whole picture for the whole 9 nights there.

On one day, our room was not cleaned and the excuse was that the hotel had too many check outs and check ins on the same day and therefore our room was not cleaned!

Only 1 bottle water is allocated for free for each stay, we drink the tap water anyway, seems a bit mean to save money this way. Cleaner will not take the empty bottle away, left it on the floor, wondering why, or reminding us the free one is consumed!

Asked for ironing board and iron, and only the ironing board is brought to our room, why no one will think the reason for getting an ironing board in the first place.

The water pressure of the bath is very low for both suites, it is like a trickling stream, so if you want to have a bath , plan it at least half an hour ahead.

Notified the Manager of all the above issues, we got an offer to have 2 glasses of champagne at the Bar downstairs, we didn't take it.

On the last day of the first stay, we brought up especially the internet and TV issues to Emilie and she offered to upgrade us to Aurore for the second stay, she went away for holiday the day after and when we checked in for the second stay, no one was aware of the offer and there was no Manager for the whole second stay when we were there, front desk staff were overworked, they were not supposed to make decisions such as TV or internet repairs and we were promised that Alexi (another Manager) will come to follow up with us and it never happened, we tried to email their corporate email addresses and no one replies.

Also, the lobster sculpture on the top floor outside Aurore has all the right limbs broken, it is not a good look, it should be repaired or replaced. I can see scuff marks and wear tears on carpets and walls, the conditions should be better considering this is a relatively new 'luxury' hotel.

In a word, enjoy the stay and don't expect any offer of help if the Manager is not onsite.

The 3 stars I gave are mainly for the comfortable bed and spacious suite.

This is one of our favorite hotels of all time. It's a beautiful boutique hotel in the heart of Le Marais. It is immaculately clean and comfortable and the staff are all very friendly and helpful. We booked a suite to have extra space for the week. The bed was so comfortable! The location is fantastic with a lot of wonderful restaurants, cafes and shopping. I highly recommend it!

The 9Confidentiel hotel is in a central location just at the edge of Marais. There are plenty of cafes, restaurants and shops close by. And you can pretty much walk everywhere from the hotel. The only thing that let us down was the breakfast; its not worth paying for. Id now choose to book without breakfast.

Thoroughly enjoyed our stay. The hotel is beautiful and right in the heart of the Marais. The rooms were bright, clean and well laid out. Staff was friendly and helpful. I would definitely stay here again.

Only two staff managing this property. But they all spoke fluent English and were very very helpful. The rooms were modern and had a rain shower in the en-suite. Toilet had multiple bidet options which for Asians was very meaningful. Will def stay again when in Paris

We loved 9 Confidential! So beautiful and attention to detail from the interior design to the petit dejeuner. The location was perfect as we have been to Paris many times and Le Marais is a great place to stay, close to unique shopping and dining with ease to the Metro.

Fantastic hotel in the middle of the Marais. Lots of cafes / restaurants across street and steps away from hotel. Rooms comfortable and great staff. While I stayed for business, would definitely come back with my family to stay.

While I can't fault the hotel location and its interesting decor, our weekend experience staying at 9Confidentiel was disappointing. On arrival, there were no large towels in our room and reception had none spare. The lift was broken throughout our stay, which meant climbing 5 flights of stairs every time. Finally the water in the shower was lukewarm - the hotel staff kept saying it was hot and it must be me not using the shower properly. All in all a mediocre experience at very high price,

Terrible experience. No staff and everything is broken. Smallest room weve ever stayed. Poor customer service. Have to lug bags up stairs because elevator is broken and no plan on fixing. Nobody working to assist. All services closed. No space for clothing. No sink in bathroom. Broken television. My mind is blown that they have any good reviews. Tried to switch to different room, but never received a call back on every attempt.

Upon arrival, we were a little put off by the unused wooden "cafe" structure blocking the street entry to the hotel. We sat there a couple of times during our stay, but it's a bit neglected, looks a little like a corral, and never mentioned by staff. A courtyard would have been really lovely.

Once you enter 9Confidentiel, though, you see what a gem it is. So tastefully designed in a modern-meets-Art Deco style with dusty pinks, brass, and mirrors - we enjoyed the small lobby several times during our stay. There were four staff members in reception throughout our stay and each one was attentive, helpful, unobtrusive, pleasant, and efficient. While my friend and I never ate in the restaurant, our husbands liked it enough to have breakfast there twice. The elevator was a bit of a joke - very, very tiny! - though it was always working (slowly). The stairwells were very clean and well-lit, so we used those occasionally.

We stayed in the "Renee" on the 5th floor (loved how the rooms were named for alluring women in framed, hazy, b&w photos) and our friends were in the "Jeanne" on the 6th. They were the same 'basic' class of room but were a little different. Ours was in the front of the hotel and had a bay window with a long sofa underneath, which was a great place to sit and put your things. There was a tiny table and one chair, as well as a corner stool. The light and airy yellow room was a little marred by a massive flatscreen on the wall. Definitely affected the vibe of the decor and was just not proportional (tiny room/giant tv).

The windows let in so much light, especially on the 5th floor - I wouldn't have wanted to be any lower for that reason, in addition to the major street noise from the restaurants, especially on Friday/Saturday. The windows did a really good job of blocking it out, but I'm not sure that would be possible on the 2nd or 3rd floor. Our friends' room on the 6th floor faced the back of the hotel, so it was completely quiet and had a really charming rooftop view. Ours faced apartments across the rue du Roi de Secile, but the window coverings in our room were incredible. They were blackout, heavy, but a natural texture you didn't mind touching (lol) and the best part - fully automated via a little retro-James Bond switch next to the bed! Genius. Besides the low, comfortable beds and the great water pressure, these motorized curtains were the best feature of the room!

The bedding was so soft and the duvet just the right weight - it all made for lovely sleeping from night one. I will say that that Housekeeping was supposed to change sheets after the third night, but ours did not do it until the fourth. The lamp lighting was also perfect in the room - no bright overheads, which I despise in hotel rooms - but also included the coolest bedside reading lights operated by just moving them up and down. It just felt very Sean Connery-era Bond for some reason. So many wonderful details make 9Confidentiel feel very special.

Our room was completely covered in mirrors (not so the 6th floor room, which did not have a bay window or a couch) but were a bit fogged...mirrors, mirrors everywhere, but not one you can do your makeup with. Our closet/bathroom area was in form of a very short hall when you walk in - the closet wasn't much more than some hooks, hangers, and a curtain. The minibar was decent, but when it wasn't replenished, the bar downstairs bent over backwards to deliver a replacement.

I'm pretty sure I've never reviewed a hotel toilet before, but this one glowed! I was the perfect light to, um, leave on at night. The shower 'room' is the one major design flaw. There is no slant or trough in the flooring to direct the water to the drain. As a result, it's like a guaranteed minor room flood the first time you use it. Pro tip: roll up a towel and place it inside the shower door (it's a big heavy door, not glass - kind of like showering in a closet). It will be soaked, but Housekeeping is used to it and they'll replace them daily. The shower itself is luxurious - a rain shower head and two others, each with constant hot temperatures and fantastic water pressure. The hotel is inexplicably stingy on the shower amenities - no lotion, no conditioner, just lots of shower gel and the occasional tiny bottle of shampoo. I'm sure they would have given us more if asked. The towels might be the only huge thing at 9Confidentiel (well, except for the tv) - they were soft, bright white, and fluffy. Delish.

A unique feature of the room was a sliding wall that closed off the bed area! Fantastic. We used this several times when my husband had to get up early for a trip to Normandy or an early breakfast. The room on the 6th floor didn't have one of these, although it did have a slightly bigger entry hall with a proper closet. The bathroom and shower room were in another small hallway at the foot of the bed, so it made it seem a little more separated from the sleeping area, which was nice, though a bit dark as it was windowless. It did have a sweet little vanity at the end, though.

Overall, this is a small gem of a hotel with lots of fantastic design details and a few minor flaws. The location is superb for key Paris destinations - and if you are looking for a lively, trendy, crowded area with loads of restaurants, bars, glace, macaron, and chocolat shops, clothing boutiques, this is the place. There's really nothing else quite like it in the city that we've found.

Our favorite spots were Le Boulangerie du Marais right on the corner, across the street. Sonam was so friendly and kind - and they had the best yogurt, croissants, tea, and pain chocolat. The pharmacy further up the street was incredibly efficient for Covid tests if you need one to return to your home country. We also liked the Portuguese cafe (Comme a Lisbon) and Pozzetto Gelato directly across from the hotel and our friends enjoyed the Cafe Suzette nearby when they couldn't get into the popular Breizh. In fact, I wish we'd explored more of the restaurants nearby - so many of every description, you probably can't go wrong.

I hadn't stayed in the Marais in 30 years and it's changed so dramatically from an old, quiet, cobblestoned charming area into a super lively, hip, trendy area filled with endless shops and restaurants. It's family-friendly, gay-friendly, and filled with people. You can see why it's become a destination area for tourists (in addition to its proximity to the Louvre, Notre Dame, Hotel de Ville, the d'Orsay, Pont Neuf, etc.) and locals on weekends. It can also make it really congested - if you don't like crowds, I mean major, spilling-into-the-streets, knock-you-off-the-sidewalk, squeeze-by-you crowds, you might want to stay elsewhere. I think the younger you are, the more you'd really love it. And we did thoroughly enjoy our stay at 9Confidentiel, as did our friends, but next time my husband and I might consider another area of the city for that reason and make a day of the Marais instead.

Hotel 9Confidential was a lovely surprise. It exceeded all expectation and if not for the lovely weather and the perfect location, I would have been happy to stay all day in my hotel room. As it was, I was happily able to visit my favourite places for books, dumplings, shoes, and of course all the delectable sites of the Marais. Will happily book a stay there again.

Great location in the marais, beautifully clean. Friendly staff from the reception to the bar.
The beds are so comfortable and the bedding is lovely. Cant wait to go back. We are already planning our next visit.

I cannot recommend 9confidentiel highly enough! We stayed in the club room, which was spacious with a comfy kind bed, a room length comfy chair/couch under the windows facing the street, a little dining area, and a wonderful view into the bustling street below. The bathroom was awesome - super clean, modern appliances and fixtures, great water pressure, 3 different showerhead options, toilet with remote controlled bidet. Towels were large, clean, fluffy, they provided bathrobes and fuzzy room slippers. Room came with a mini bar that we used to keep champagne slightly chilled as well, an illy espresso machine, tea kettle (espresso pods and tea bags provided and replaced by housekeeping daily). We had a seamless check-in and check-out experience and staff were on hand 24/7 to assist with anything we needed. I think we'll stay here every time we visit Paris in the future!

Well located. Walking distance to attractions, shopping and restaurants. Vey comfortable beds. Staff very accommodating especially the young lady, she helped us find our way to PSG stadium for a game.

Amenities and location of this hotel are top notch. Honestly one of the best places Ive ever stayed. The hotel staff were also extremely welcoming and warm, and the room was the perfect size. The shower was unbelievably nice.

Positives - great location, 10 min walk to Notre Dame, similar to Louvre, close to river, close to nice places to eat/drink in La Marais. Staff were friendly and responsive. Hotel was clean and room made up well every day.
Would be better if - a money-hungry manager somewhere made the penny-pinching idea that guests only get two coffee pods and two tea bags included. You want more, you have to pay. Absolutely bizarre petty decision and sends a very negative message about the higher management of the hotel. Lift was out of order a couple of times during our stay. Limited room service.
Overall, we had a good stay and it's a solid 4*.

Excellent location and perfect design. The communal areas and rooms are very pretty. Very comfortable bed. Everything looks relatively new. Polite reception staff.

Cleanliness of the rooms can be improved - bathroom was not as clean as it should be. Coffee capsules in the room are charged after the first night which is surprising for a 4* hotel. Our room was not cleaned on the second day - when we asked about it, we were told that the cleaners forgot. We had to ask reception for additional shampoo, shower gels and toilet rolls as the cleaners would not replace the empty ones. Details that definitely need to be improved to justify the relatively high price.

Great location but no heating in rooms.
I got sick.
No heating in winter in Paris in such a hotel is unacceptable.
I would not recommend this hotel, as you wont be able to sleep in such conditions, at least not in winter, and not what you expect for this level

I had a starstruck when I got into myself and had to check if booking ratewas correct. The room looked stunning and the hotel was located near everywhere. The staff was very friendly and helpful. I liked the design of the hotel the most.

Confortable, elegant, well-located. Very friendly staff. Truly enjoyable experience. It is situated in an ideal location, very close to everything. You can walk to the Opera Bastille or the Louvre easily.

Perfect, location is great, well could not be better, hotel super nice. we all love the rooms!
the mega service women in charge of breakfast very very nice and the guy in the bar great.
thats from now on our Paris home;-) <3

Awesome room on courtyard side so it was incredibly quiet. Beautiful furnishings, very upscale. Very large room. We LOVED the location, in the middle of the action and scene of Marais. Convenient to metro, bus, and taxis. Great restaurants on every corner plus just some great grab n go. The staff was very friendly, helpful, knowledgeable, and accommodating. And a great and varied breakfast with some wonderful staff.

It was lovely to be back after 18 months. The staffs are always helpful and friendly. Love how clean and bright the room is. The location is also great, many shops are around. I will be back again to stay!

Great location, best part was the thick walls and windows. Very quiet location was good too with multiple buses and subway to choose from. Would recommend this hotel to couples. The rooms maybe too small for large families.

Excellent location, really friendly and helpful staff, beautiful decor (loved the window sofa in our room), lovely bedding and comfortable bed, nice bar and lobby, great shower (and toiletries). We can't wait to go back.

Amazing emplacement and amazing decoration and atmosphere.
A form of time travel with a theme of 20's stars in harmony with the architecture of the building. the rooms are extremely comfortable, full of light, the bedding fantastic, a refined decoration with a touch of ethnic ... A must to experience in this area

A small and elegant Hotel, very stylish and cosy at the same time. The rooms are very comfortable and clean. Windows closed, you don't hear anything from the busy Marais District. There are lots of restaurants in the neighborhood, Forum Les Halles, Centre Pompidou, Ile de la Cit, Louvre in walking distance. We really enjoyed our stay and would highly recommend this place.

Great hotel and service, amazing location. Staff is amazingly friendly. The bar is super cool and they make great cocktails. Immaculate conditions in the room. Beautiful rooms and amazing toiletries. Great for kids too.

Our stay at 9Confidentiel was excellent from beginning to end. Upon arrival, my niece and I were upgraded to a larger room. The bed was very comfortable, we loved the shower, and the staff was incredibly friendly. I would definitely stay here again!

Everything about my stay was beyond my expectation. The location, first of all, is one of the best in Paris, in close proximity to countless restaurants and shops. The attention to detail in hotel is great, lobby / lounge area with food and drink service is nice. High speed internet works great and is very consistent. Hotel staff were kind and courteous.

Though I've at many hotels in Paris over the years, I look forward to returning to 9Confidential again in the future.

Very nice boutique hotel in a great location. Friendly staff and nice amenities. Highly recommend for couples, tourists. This is not a business hotel. There are bistros and clubs nearby, so get a higher floor if youre a light sleeper.

First, let me start by saying I searched Trip Advisor for a highly rated Parisian hotel in the 4th Arr with a Fitness Center. This hotel came up in my search and the reviews were outstanding. However, upon arrival I learned that there was NO Fitness Center on-site and you had to walk about 10 minutes to reach one and pay 25 per visit. This was very disappointing and Trip Advisor should adjust their settings to say they Do Not have a fitness center. I cannot say enough good things about Paul, the concierge. He was outstanding! He was very friendly and extremely helpful from booking a tour to dining recommendations. He was the highlight of the hotel. The rooms are small and well appointed, but missing a few basic items like lotion. The front desk staff was very kind, but they made several mistakes ranging from putting a deposit/ hold on my credit card and then losing it, to ordering the taxi to take me to the airport at the wrong time, despite an extended discussion. Thankfully, Sandra, the morning desk assistant, was able to sort it all out and order me another taxi that arrived in 15 minutes. Overall, the small staff is very kind and strive hard to make your stay comfortable. Their location in the Marais district cant be beat. The neighborhood is very vibrant with lots of restaurants and shopping, although the old feel of years passed is changing due to the increasingly high rents, forcing out the independently owned small cafes and stores. It is a very easy walk to most places. You can get to most of the major tourist attractions in less than 40 minutes walking, or take the Metro. Just dont stay here if you are seeking a fitness center on-site. And be sure to ask Paul for recommendations!

This hotel was absolutely amazing! My husband and I had a red eye flight and an hour and a half taxi ride from CDG airport and the second we arrived at the hotel, we were met with sincere, helpful Paul the concierge. Honestly he may have been the best part of our stay, haha. Thank you Paul for all your assistance in helping us with our bags, giving us recommendations etc. So great! Ok the hotel's scent was so grand.They upgraded us to an executive room which was such great news. The bath products were local and luxurious, bed was soft, towels were fluffy and not rough. Love the decore of the rooms, soft yellow with rose gold mirrors. Our room was facing the courtyard area and was super quiet.Thank you for such a lovely stay.

For the second year in a row we had a marvelous stay. The location is amazing and the hotel is wonderful. We were upgraded to a club room that was spacious and comfortable. The bar is very expensive but there are great cafes in the area. We hope to return next year!

It has been a long time since I felt that a review must be written. The 9 Confidential is located in the Marre in Paris which is a lively young vibrant region with many attractions to pull you out of the perfect room with the exquisite service and out of this world decor. The hotel is clean, the bar is hospitable and Paul the concierge is the best. You can walk anywhere and enjoy the sites around or take the metro in hotel de ville station,that is if they are not on strike. The Resturants around the hotel are very good, the Philosoph,JaJa and many more. Dont miss the Jazz club around the corner. 58Riv. Enjoy

Five star hotels are something different. Staff extremely reduced and not particularly professional, breakfast inadequate, room non comfortable enough : to be generous, 4 stars are enough
The location is in a very beautiful part of the city, and this is the only plus

Great location in the center of Paris, attentive and complete staff, unique and relaxed decor in both the public spaces and the room, very comfortable bed and large bathroom, quiet, ...my stay could not have been better !

We had an amazing stay in the hotel. Everyone was very friendly and professional. The room was clean, big and well decorated. The breakfast was great. We did not missed anything.

The location is perfect. Within one minute you are standing in the main road towards the Champs Elysee.

We stayed here for four days with our young toddler. Staff were very friendly, the concierge always offers to help with everything and every night we request milk for our toddler and they send it up complimentary.

Could not speak more highly of this boutique hotel. Location is amazing minutes from shops, metro and restaurants.

We had 48 hours in Paris and decided to book here. Great hotel, lovely location in the middle of wonderful restaurants and cafes. Hotel is a gem - just a year old and beautifully decorated. We were pleasantly surprised and upgraded upon arrival to the Jaqueline Room (#11). Check-In was a breeze with Sandra - she was extremely accommodating. There is a cute little bar on-site and we grabbed some champagne with our lovely bartender, Camilla. She was super helpful and shared some of her favorite spots to visit (which we did). There is a restaurants onsite that offered brunch but we chose to go out and experience the city. Everyone was super friendly.We will definitely be back!

Perfect place to stay, you will not be disappointed. Location is central with all transport links such as Metro close by. Staff excellent. Breakfast very very very good and the waiter was most attentive.

Great boutique hotel, friendly staff and cute rooms. Bedding was ok, but overall experience was top notch. Location was perfect with lots of restaurants and shopping nearby. I would stay here for a holiday as well, highly recommend.

Brilliant hotel, chic decor, comfortable and clean, lounge and bar area very chilled friendly and helpful staff, gave lots of information for sightseeing, great location with bars, restaurants and artisan shops.

I am a Philippe Starck fan. I loved the little design details of this hotel. Very chic, helpful staff etc. However, it was noisy! I'm not talking about regular street noises or ambulances-I'm talking about club music past 2am. After the first night, Saturday, I mentioned the noise to the girl at the front desk. She apologized and said ear plugs were available. I didn't not grab any because I was hoping the club music was an isolated incident. Unfortunately, no. At 1am on Sunday night I was still up listening to club music. If your hotel is in downtown Paris, it seems like Hoteling 101 to provide decent soundproof windows. This is a lovely hotel, but if you can't get a decent nights sleep due to noisy club music, is it worth it?

As soon as you cross the threshold youre transported by a beautiful other worldly scent. The lobby is small but incredibly cozy and inviting. Czech in was a breeze. The room is a jewel ox. A reimagined boudoir cleverly made to Look much larger by use of mirrors is the perfect sanctuary from the bustling streets of the Marais. The bed was a silky winder, the shower was decedent. Id return in a heartbeat.

The best thing about this hotel is not that it has stylish clean rooms and is steps away from everything -- though these things are important. It is the elegant little bar tucked between the reception room and the lounge. There, you will find world-class cocktails prepared by charming mixologists who really know what they are doing. The staff generally is top notch, which often makes all the difference.

This hotel is in such a great location for visiting Paris. It is near many good restaurants and cafes. We stayed in for breakfast each day and were very happy with the food! The hotel is beautifully decorated and the staff are absolutely superb at their jobs!! The room was super comfortable. We had some people traveling with us who were not happy with the fact that they had to share the same bed (with two quilts on it - quite odd) so I would recommend if you are traveling with a friend, be sure you know each other well because you will literally be in bed together in a double occupancy room.

Stayed here on honeymoon 20th to 23rd September. Amazing hotel, in a great location. Only downfall is we were charged 1,550 on check in and 1,250.10 On check out. We were advised on check in there was 100 euro per night for extra fees precharged (mini bar) and it wouldn't be taken. I know the 1,550 will be refunded in a few days but could be organised better by the hotel like they charge for what you actually use or explain it a bit better. Luckily I had extra money in my account just in case. Cocktails named Jeanne are amazing. We had them every night. Will definitely stay again next time we visit Paris

Had a wonderful time at this hotel. The staff was very kind and accommodating and the location was wonderful. Shopping and restaurants near by, very close metro that can take you to all the main sightseeing locations. Rooms a little tight but we would definitely recommend this hotel.

Excellent stay at 9Confidential. The room was clean and quiet and the staff were all extremely friendly. The location is great - there are cafes & restaurants close by, a grocery store around the corner and bus stop and metro stops within a few blocks. Would definitely stay here again our next visit to Paris.

Loved staying at 9Confidential. The entire staff was the best. Incredibly nice. The room was so cool and comfy. Linen, amenities, location were exceptional! Best shower in Paris! Lol. I would come back in a second! And the alcove windows in the room were so Parisian and made this stay even more memorable! Thank you.

Excellent boutique hotel - exquisite and good value. Staff is stellar and so very friendly. This is in a perfect location. The rooms are spacious and in perfect condition. Charming little bar. Only suggestion is to serve drinks a little more quickly.

Outstanding hotel in heart of Marais. Chic, with stunning design, well trained team. Very luxurious and comfortable bedrooms provide top quality sleep. Informal, cool atmosphere. Highly recommended location with surrounded by cool bars and restaurants. This is authentic Paris.

This is a nicest and firendliest hotel in Paris. Location is AMAZING, right in the center of the trendiest area of Paris (Le Marais). Interior design is hyper chic en sophisticated and everything is super comfortable. it is a small hotel but you feel like in a Palace with a conierge, a doorman, a bar serving delicious cocktail...
